agreed_on_going_public_at":"2014-06-11T08:54:01.900Z","team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":null,"comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"**Industry Standard Procedure**\r\nWhen the password is changed or email address has been updated for any particular account,all the sessions which were active with the old password/email should be destroyed.\r\n**Reason**\r\nIf somehow anybody hacked into your account and you understand that someone has trespassed into your account,then what will you do?You will change your password to secure your account.But in relateIQ changing the password doesnot destroys the other sessions which are logged in with old passwords.So,your account remains insecure even after the changing of password.\r\n","weakness":{"id":27,"name":"Improper Authentication - Generic"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2014-05-29T22:47:17.674Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-232554579.49394128,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":0,"voters":[],"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"activities":[{"id":40801,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Thank you for submitting this bug! We're looking into it and will get back to you shortly.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2014-04-28T21:02:11.194Z","updated_at":"2014-04-28T21:02:11.194Z","actor":{"username":"im_in_france","cleared":false,"url":"/im_in_france","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"relateiq","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":41812,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugInformative","message":"Hi we only allow 2 sessions to be active in the account this has been verified and is under normal design. If you feel this is wrong and a serious issue please let us know. As of right now we've decided to not change this funtionality. ","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2014-04-29T22:47:17.714Z","updated_at":"2014-04-29T22:47:17.714Z","actor":{"username":"johnfiedler","cleared":false,"url":"/johnfiedler","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"relateiq","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":44771,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"I do feel that this is wrong.Its your policy to active two sessions at a time.But the second session should be destroyed once the password is been changed.This is the industry standard.I explained why the session should be destroyed.The same bug was affecting hackerone also.And when it was reported they resolved the issue.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2014-05-06T10:16:46.169Z","updated_at":"2014-05-06T10:16:46.169Z","actor":{"username":"siddiki","cleared":true,"url":"/siddiki","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/003/502/cf522f55c77430ca80c9ff947d022eb7e3d79350_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"relateiq","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":49868,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Even you can take the example of Facebook also.Once the password is changed,all the old sessions are destroyed to keep the account safe.\nAgain explaining:\nSuppose someone hacked into my account,and started monitoring my activities silently.